# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Added

- Initial release of `palisade_errors` crate
- Core error handling with automatic zeroization
- Error code namespace system (CORE, CFG, DCP, TEL, COR, RSP, LOG, PLT, IO)
- Dual display modes (internal forensics vs external sanitization)
- Sensitive data handling with explicit marking
- Zero-allocation logging paths
- Lifetime-bound log entries
- Convenience macros for error creation
- Metadata support for incident tracking
- `trusted_debug` feature for development environments
- `external_signaling` feature (reserved for future use)
- Comprehensive documentation and examples

### Security

- All error context automatically zeroized on drop
- Separation of error kinds and sensitive paths
- No information leakage in Display implementation
- DoS protection via field length truncation

## [0.1.0] - 2026-01-06

Initial release.
